      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an older lab like yours, a good target ratio is often around 30-40% protein and keeping fat moderate, perhaps in the 25-30% range. This balance supports maintaining lean muscle mass while managing overall caloric intake for weight control. It's always wise to consult with a veterinarian to fine-tune the exact breakdown based on your lab's specific activity level and health status.",
      "source": "target",
