    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. one more thing, sometimes i see stuff like \"animal by-products\" or \"meat meal\" on these labels and i can't tell if that's actually good or if it's just filler. is that stuff usually okay for an older dog's protein needs or should i try to avoid it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Meat meal\" and \"animal by-products\" are just ingredients, so the quality varies greatly; some are excellent protein sources, while others can be lower quality. For an older dog, prioritizing whole meat sources and specific named protein (like \"chicken meal\") is generally preferable, as it offers more complete nutrition. If you are concerned, look for brands that list identifiable, named animal proteins near the top of the ingredient list.",
      "source": "target",
